title.narrative: To reduce malaria incidence and deaths by at least 75 percent of the 2016 levels by 2023, working towards a malaria-free Kenya

description.narrative: Kenya - Malaria - National Treasury of the Republic of Kenya - TNT. This program has the following goals: To reduce morbidity and mortality caused by malaria in the various epidemiological zones by two thirds of the 2015 level by 2020. The objectives of this program are: To have at least 80% of people living in malaria risk areas using appropriate malaria preventive interventions by 2020. To have 100% of all suspected malaria cases presenting to a health provider managed according to the national malaria treatment guidelines by 2020. To have at least 80% of people living in malaria risk areas using appropriate malaria preventive interventions by 2020. To increase utilization of all malaria control interventions by target communities in Kenya to at least 80% by 2020 and sustain thereafter. Ensure that all levels (national, counties, sub-counties) provide reports on at least 80% of core malaria indicators according to the national M & E plan by 2020. To increase capacity in coordination, leadership, governance and resource mobilization at all levels towards achievement of the malaria program objectives by 2020
